HEADWORD: Webbed
<hw>Webbed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Provided
with a web.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the toes united by a
membrane, or web; <as>as, the <ex>webbed</ex> feet of aquatic
fowls</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Webber</ent>⟦br⟧
